{"title_page": "Central Bus Terminus, Erode", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{citation style|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Central Bus Terminus {{R-I|bus}}\n| cta_header          =\n| type                =\n| style               =\n| image               = \n| image_size          =\n| image_caption       =\n| hangul              =\n| hanja               =\n| rr                  =\n| mr                  =\n| address             = Sathy Road, [[Erode]].\n| country             = [[India]]\n| coordinates         = {{Coord|11.3470|77.7197|type:landmark_region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           =\n| line                =\n| other               =\n| structure           =\n| platform            = 13 (100 Bays)\n| depth               =\n| levels              =\n| tracks              =\n| parking             = Yes\n| bicycle             = \n| baggage_check       =\n| opened              = {{Start date and age|1973|df=y}}<ref name=built>{{cite news|title=Erode Municipal Central Bus Stand to get facelift|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2005/12/20/stories/2005122004650300.htm|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=20 December 2005|location=Erode}}</ref>\n| closed              =\n| rebuilt             =\n| electrified         =\n| ADA                 = {{Access icon|20px}}\n| code                = ERO ([[State Express Transport Corporation (Tamil Nadu)|SETC]])<br>IRD ([[Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation|KSRTC]])\n| owned               = [[Erode Municipal Corporation]]\n| operator            = [[Department of Transport (Tamil Nadu)]]\n| zone                =\n| smartcardname       =\n| smartcardstatus     =\n| former              =\n| passengers          = \n| pass_year           =\n| pass_percent        =\n| pass_system         =\n| mpassengers         =\n| services            = 1,200 services per day\n| map_locator         =\n| route_map           =\n| map_state           =\n}}\n\nThe '''Central Bus Terminus''', is the main bus station complex in the City of [[Erode]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. It is located near the Swastik Circle at the junction of [[National Highway 544H (India)|NH-544H]], [[National Highway 381A (India)|NH-381A]] and [[State Highway 15 (Tamil Nadu)|State Highway 15]] about 3&nbsp;km north of [[Erode Junction]]. It is the third largest bus terminus in Tamil Nadu followed by CMBT and Madurai Mattuthavani bus stand.\n\n==History==\nThe Central Bus Terminus was opened to public in 1973 and christened ''Independence day Silver Jubilee Memorial Bus Terminus'' to commemorate the [[Silver Jubilee]] celebrations of the [[Independence Day (India)|Indian Independence]]. It is located at the heart of the City, with two Entry and two Exit Gates. It was constructed and being maintained by [[Erode Municipal Corporation]]. The available space in the terminal was spread over an area of {{convert|12|acre|m2}} and had parking bays to accommodate more than 200 buses simultaneously. Around 1lakh passengers are catered by more than 1,500 services that are operated from the terminal every day.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erode busstand to be modernised|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/erode-bus-stand-to-be-modernised/article3167998.ece|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=23 March 2006|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\n==Operations==\nThe terminal caters to both intra-city and intercity services with 13 platforms. Buses ply from here to all major towns in [[Tamil Nadu]] and other important places in [[Karnataka]], [[Kerala]], [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Puducherry]]. The terminus operates with three stations namely, Mofussil Bus Station, Town Bus Station and Minibus Station.\n\n{| class =\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Platform!!Bus Route\n|-\n|1|| Buses in Queue / Halt\n|-\n|2|| [[Coimbatore]], [[Tirupur]], [[Ooty]], [[Chennai]], [[Bengaluru]], [[Tirupati (city)|Tirupati]], [[Ernakulam]], [[Puducherry]], [[Palani]], [[Mysuru]], [[Gobichettipalayam]]\n|-\n|3|| [[Karur]], [[Trichy]], [[Madurai]], [[Tirunelveli]], [[Rameshwaram]], [[Thanjavur]], [[Velankanni]], [[Kumbakonam]], [[Mayiladuthurai]], [[Kanyakumari]], [[Oddanchatram]]\n|-\n|4|| [[Salem, Tamil Nadu|Salem]], [[Namakkal]], [[Vilupuram]], [[Rasipuram]], [[Cuddalore]], [[Vellore]], [[Attur]], [[Kallakurichi]], [[Chidambaram]]\n|-\n|5||[[Dharmapuri]], [[Bhavani, Erode|Bhavani]], [[Anthiyur]], [[Mettur]], [[Ammapettai, Erode|Ammapettai]], [[Mecheri]]\n|-\n|6|| City bus services towards [[Perundurai]], [[Chennimalai]], [[Arachalur]], [[Sivagiri, Erode|Sivagiri]], [[Solar, Erode|Solar]]\n|-\n|7, 8|| City bus services towards [[Bhavani, Erode|Bhavani]], [[Komarapalayam]], [[Chithode]], [[BP Agraharam]], [[Pallipalayam]], [[Tiruchengode]], [[Sankagiri]]\n|-\n|9, 10|| City bus services\n|-\n|11|| City bus services towards [[Erode Junction]], [[Erode|P.S.Park]], [[Surampatti]], [[Erode|Periyar G.H]]\n|-\n|12, 13|| Intra-city mini bus services\n|}\n\n==Facilities==\n[[File:Layout of CBS, Erode.jpg|thumb|Layout of Central Bus Terminus, Erode]]\nThe bus terminus have been modernized with concrete flooring, high mast lamps and the introduction of various extension counters, e-governance facilities and bank ATMs.<ref>{{cite news|title=Railway, TNEB counters to be set up in Erode bus stand|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/Railway-TNEB-counters-to-be-set-up-in-Erode-bus-stand/article14752678.ece|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=21 April 2007|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\nAn air conditioned passenger waiting hall, a reverse osmosis water treatment plant and a separate station for mini-buses are in operation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Drinking water promised to bus passengers|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/Drinking-water-promised-to-bus-passengers/article14780115.ece|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=20 June 2007|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref> An underground parking facility has been constructed for two-wheelers and a multi level shopping complex has been developed along with additional public convenience facilities inside the complex.<ref>{{cite news|title=Newly built buildings remain unutilised in Erode town|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/newly-built-buildings-remain-unutilised-in-erode-town/article2364042.ece|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=17 August 2011|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\n==Plans for the future==\nThe bus station handles about more than 1200 buses every day. Due to the increasing number of services, the bus station is nearing its full operating capacity. And the core-centric location of the terminus causes heavy traffic congestion on the narrow city roads.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erode may get another bus terminal|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/Erode-may-get-another-bus-terminal/article15977810.ece\n|accessdate=3 Feb 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=4 February 2010|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\nSo, the Corporation is planning to construct two satellite bus terminals at [[Solar, Erode|Solar]] (Erode South) and [[Chithode]] (Erode North) to share the handling of intercity bus services as a measure to reduce the traffic flow in core city.\n<ref>{{cite news|title=Erode Corporation keenly pursuing satellite bus stand projects|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/erode-corporation-keenly-pursuing-satellite-bus-stand-projects/article7650299.ece|accessdate=3 February 2015|newspaper=The Hindu|date=14 September 2015|location=Erode, India}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Transport in Erode]]\n* [[Erode Ring Road]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Erode district}}\n\n[[Category:Bus stations in Erode|C]]\n[[Category:Transport in Erode]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{citation style|date=