ped along with additional public convenience facilities inside the complex.<ref>{{cite news|title=Newly built buildings remain unutilised in Erode town|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/newly-built-buildings-remain-unutilised-in-erode-town/article2364042.ece|accessdate=3 February 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=17 August 2011|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\n==Plans for the future==\nThe bus station handles about more than 1200 buses every day. Due to the increasing number of services, the bus station is nearing its full operating capacity. And the core-centric location of the terminus causes heavy traffic congestion on the narrow city roads.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erode may get another bus terminal|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/Erode-may-get-another-bus-terminal/article15977810.ece\n|accessdate=3 Feb 2017|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=4 February 2010|location=[[Erode]]}}</ref>\n\nSo, the Corporation is planning to construct two satellite bus terminals at [[Solar, Erode|Solar]] (Erode South) and [[Chithode]] (Erode North) to share the handling of intercity bus services as a measure to reduce the traffic flow in core city.\n<ref>{{cite news|title=Erode Corporation keenly pursuing satellite bus stand projects|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/erode-corporation-keenly-pursuing-satellite-bus-stand-projects/article7650299.ece|accessdate=3 February 2015|newspaper=The Hindu|date=14 September 2015|location=Erode, India}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Transport in Erode]]\n* [[Erode Ring Road]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Erode district}}\n\n[[Category:Bus stations in Erode|C]]\n", "name_user": "Jaywardhan009", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Bus_Terminus,_Erode"}
